radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; normal liver, spleen, and adrenals; gallbladder normal in morphology with several dense gallstones; mild inflammatory fat stranding around pancreas; moderate amount of free fluid within pelvis; stomach collapsed; normal loops of small bowel; normal appearing bladder and prostate; colon normal with adjacent fat stranding; no evidence of acute cholecystitis; no intraperitoneal free air; no bony or soft tissue abnormality.
